trend_summary: Across the four dates the landscape remains overwhelmingly agricultural, with only small villages and farmsteads. Field patterns become slightly larger and straighter, a few hamlets expand outward, and roadside ribbon building grows modestly. New minor roads and scattered industrial-farm sheds appear, while woodland patches fluctuate but stay secondary. Overall character stays rural with sparse built-up fabric.
notable_changes: Incremental outward growth of several villages, adding new houses along access roads.
Construction of additional farm sheds and small industrial/agri units, especially near road junctions.
Field consolidation: irregular plots merged into larger rectangular fields in central and southern sectors.
Slight densification of minor road network, improving connectivity between settlements.
Localised woodland clearance and new shelterbelt plantings, altering green patch distribution.
